@{PARD}
@{B}Golem, Rat, Stone Description:@{UB}@{PAR}

A stronger variant of the Rat Golem are those carved out of stone instead of
@{" wood " LINK "ImpPro:Data/ExtMonsterData/Golem, Rat, Wood.long/main"}. These constructs are tougher than their wooden counterparts, but have the
disadvantage of being slower and heavier.@{PAR}

Rat Golems are minor constructs carved from Stone, and placed as guards. Unlike
regular golems, these are not animated by an elemental spirit, but rather that
of an animal (usually a rat). They are created in groups of five, as one rat
spirit is sufficient to animate five bodies. They are provided with instructions
upon creation (for example, "Attack any creatures entering this room"), and then
carry out this command to the best of their ability until destroyed.@{PAR}

@ENDNODE

