@{PARD}
@{B}Golem, Rat, Stone Combat:@{UB}@{PAR}

Rat Golems use pack tactics in combat, as they did in life. All five rats bound
by one spirit attack the same opponent, as it is difficult for the spirit to
divide its attention. Each Rat attacks with a bite, however there is no danger
of disease. The rats fight with blatant disregard for their own lives, except
when faced with fire. Their fear of fire is still there (which was a fear in
life), but since it is not a significant weakness, their morale does not drop.
They must make a morale check each round, however, after a display of fire.@{PAR}

Rat Golems are immune to damage from nonmagical weapons. They are similarly
immune to mind-affecting spells, such as Sleep and Charm spells. Fire-based
magic is more effective against them, doing a point less per die of damage
that it would normally inflict. Cold-based magic has no effect at all. They are
immune to Magic Missiles, but other spells affect them normally.@{PAR}

There is no chance of loosing control of the rats, as their spirits are
tightly bound to their task. However, the spirits can be dismissed from their
servitude by a Dispel Magic spell against 13th level magic.@{PAR}

@ENDNODE

